## Twitter Sentiment Analysis
A Natural Language Processing (NLP) project that analyzes sentiments (positive, negative, neutral) from real-time Twitter data using text preprocessing and machine learning techniques.

## Objective
To classify tweets based on sentiment and gain insights into public opinion using NLP and supervised learning.

## Key Features
Cleaned and preprocessed tweet text (removal of noise, tokenization, etc.)

Converted text into numerical format using TF-IDF
Built and evaluated models (Logistic Regression, Naive Bayes, etc.)
Visualized sentiment distribution and model performance

##  Tools & Libraries
Python
Pandas, Numpy
Scikit-learn
NLTK
Matplotlib, Seaborn
Jupyter Notebook

## How to Run
bash
Copy
Edit
pip install pandas numpy scikit-learn nltk matplotlib seaborn
jupyter notebook

## Sample Output
Confusion Matrix
Accuracy, Precision, Recall
Sentiment distribution plots
